---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// SEO: Schema actualizado con los datos exactos del post
const scheduleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SportsEvent",
  "name": "Official FIFA World Cup 2026 Schedule",
  "startDate": "2026-06-11",
  "endDate": "2026-07-19",
  "eventStatus": "https://schema.org/EventScheduled",
  "description": "Official dates, venues, and matchups for the 48-team FIFA World Cup 2026."
};
---

<Layout 
  title="Official FIFA World Cup 2026 Schedule: Dates, Venues & Matches" 
  description="Check the official world cup fifa 2026 schedule. Dates for the opening match, group stages, and the grand final in New Jersey."
  schema={scheduleSchema}
>
  <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-8 text-blue-900 tracking-tight">
    FIFA World Cup 2026 Schedule: Match Dates and Venues
  </h1>
  
  <article class="prose lg:prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
    <p>
      After conducting the group draw, FIFA has released the official <strong>fifa world cup 2026 schedule</strong>, including dates, times, and venues for the matches to be held in the United States, Canada, and Mexico. The event will begin on June 11 with the opening match between Mexico and South Africa at the Estadio Azteca and will conclude on Sunday, July 19, with the grand final at MetLife Stadium in New Jersey, USA.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Tournament Format and Qualified Teams</h2>
    <p>
      The 2026 World Cup will be the first to feature 104 matches and 48 participating teams. This will be the inaugural edition with 48 squads, organized into groups of four (from A to L). The top two from each group and the eight best third-placed finishers will qualify for the round of 32 in the <strong>fifa world cup 2026 schedule</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      So far, 18 teams are already confirmed: Argentina, Australia, Brazil, Canada, Colombia, South Korea, Ecuador, United States, Iran, Japan, Jordan, Morocco, Mexico, New Zealand, Paraguay, Tunisia, Uruguay, and Uzbekistan.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Host Cities and Logistics</h2>
    <p>
      FIFA has selected eleven venues in the United States (Dallas, Miami, Atlanta, Boston, Houston, Philadelphia, Los Angeles, Kansas City, New York/New Jersey, San Francisco, and Seattle), three in Mexico (Mexico City, Guadalajara, and Monterrey), and two in Canada (Toronto and Vancouver). 
    </p>
    <p>
      This tournament will feature a novel organization that prioritizes team rest and fan logistics within the <strong>fifa world cup 2026 schedule</strong>, establishing three rest days between 103 of the 104 matches. The final will take place on Sunday, July 19, at MetLife Stadium in New Jersey, while the third-place match will be played in Miami.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Group Stage Kickoff and Host Matches</h2>
    <p>
      Regarding the group stage of the <strong>fifa world cup 2026 schedule</strong>, the only teams that knew their dates and locations in advance were the hosts. Mexico will open the tournament on Thursday, June 11, at the Mexico City Stadium, popularly known as the Azteca, facing South Africa in Group A at 4:00 PM (Argentina time).
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Host Nation Debuts</h3>
    <p>
      Canada will begin its participation on Friday, June 12, in Toronto (Group B) against a rival yet to be defined, which could be Italy (at 4:00 PM, Argentina time), while the United States will also play that same day in Los Angeles (Group D) against Paraguay (starting at 10:00 PM, Argentina time). These three teams guaranteed their presence at home during the initial phase of the <strong>fifa world cup 2026 schedule</strong>.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Final Playoff Spots</h3>
    <p>
      There are still six places to be determined, which will be defined in the playoff matches in March of next year. Four of those places are for Europe and two for the international playoff. Internationally, the Democratic Republic of the Congo will fight for a spot against the winner of the clash between New Caledonia and Jamaica, while Iraq awaits the winner of the match between Suriname and Bolivia.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">European Qualifiers Path</h2>
    <p>
      Competing in the European playoffs for the remaining <strong>fifa world cup 2026 schedule</strong> slots will be Italy, Northern Ireland, Ukraine, Sweden, Turkey, Romania, Denmark, North Macedonia, Wales, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Poland, Albania, Slovakia, Kosovo, Czech Republic, and the Republic of Ireland.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>